## Steps I fallowed to perform the project
1. Initialize Terraform
   terraform init

2. Plan infrastructure
   terraform plan

3. Apply infrastructure
   terraform apply

## Connecting to Kubernetes cluster
After cluster creation:
   aws eks update-kubeconfig --region us-east-1 --name gitops-eks  

To verify nodes 
   kubectl get nodes

## Docker Setup
   I containerized my Flask application using Docker.

   docker build -t flask-app .
   docker tag flask-app mydockerhub/flask-app:latest
   docker push mydockerhub/flask-app:latest

## Jenkins CI/CD Pipeline
   Jenkins automates the entire workflow from code push to deployment.
    Pull code from GitHub
    Build Docker image
    Run tests (if any)
    Push image to Docker Hub
    Deploy Kubernetes deployment

## ArgoCD GitOps Setup
   I used ArgoCD to automatically sync Kubernetes manifests from GitHub.

## Monitoring Setup
  I used:
  Prometheus → collects metrics (CPU, memory, pods)
  Grafana → visual dashboards

## Rollback statergy
  ArgoCD rollback
  Open ArgoCD UI
  Select previous deployment version
  Click "Rollback"
